<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900703-0072</DOCNO><DOCID>900703-0072.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- GNI Group Inc.:   Firm Expects New Plant   To Boost Results Sharply</HL><DATE>07/03/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   GNUC</CO><LP>   GNI Group Inc. said the start-up and commercial operationof a new chemical resource processing plant will result in anearly 40% increase in both revenue and net income for thefiscal year ending June 30, 1991.   For the year ended June 30, 1989, the Houston companyreported a loss of $75,000, or two cents a share, on revenueof about $12.5 million. Results for the period included a$550,000 charge related to the write-down of assets. Thecompany expects to release earnings for fiscal 1990 in earlyAugust.</LP><TEXT>   Located at GNI's Deer Park, Texas, complex, the plantprovides waste reclamation and custom processing services forthe chemical and petrochemical industries.</TEXT></DOC>